{"title_page": "Roman Catholic Archdiocese of San Antonio", "text_new": "{{Infobox diocese\n| jurisdiction      = Archdiocese<!-- Type of jurisdiction: i.e. Diocese or Archdiocese -->\n| name              = San Antonio\n| latin             = Archidioecesis Sancti Antonii\n| local             = <!-- Name in the Spanish language -->Arquidi\u00f3cesis de San Antonio\n| image             = San Fernando Cathedral.jpg\n| image_size        = 250px \n| image_alt         = \n| caption           = San Fernando Cathedral\n| coat              = Roman Catholic Archdiocese of San Antonio.svg\n| coat_size         = 150px \n<!---- Locations ---->\n| country           = [[United States]]\n| territory         = City of [[San Antonio, Texas|San Antonio]] and the following counties: [[Val Verde County, Texas|Val Verde]], [[Edwards County, Texas|Edwards]], [[Kerr County, Texas|Kerr]], [[Gillespie County, Texas|Gillespie]], [[Kendall County, Texas|Kendall]], [[Comal County, Texas|Comal]], [[Guadalupe County, Texas|Guadalupe]], [[Gonzales County, Texas|Gonzales]], [[Uvalde County, Texas|Uvalde]], [[Kinney County, Texas|Kinney]], [[Medina County, Texas|Medina]], [[Bexar County, Texas|Bexar]], [[Wilson County, Texas|Wilson]], [[Karnes County, Texas|Karnes]], [[Frio County, Texas|Frio]], [[Atascosa County, Texas|Atascosa]], and [[McMullen County, Texas|McMullen]].\n| province          = [[List of the Roman Catholic dioceses of the United States#Ecclesiastical province of San Antonio|Province of San Antonio]]\n| coordinates       = <!-- Use {{coord}} --> \n<!---- Statistics ---->\n| area_sqmi         = 27841<!-- Area in square miles, automatically converted -->\n| population        = 2,458,351\n| population_as_of  = 2014\n| catholics         = 728,001<ref>http://www.archsa.org/fast_facts.aspx</ref><!-- Number of Catholics in the diocese -->\n| catholics_percent = 29.6\n| parishes          = 139\n| churches          = <!-- Number of churches in the diocese -->\n| congregations     = <!-- Number of congregations in the diocese -->\n| schools           = <!-- Number of church supported schools in the diocese -->\n| members           = <!-- Number of members in the diocese -->\n<!---- Information ---->\n| denomination      = [[Catholic]]\n| rite              = [[Roman Rite]]\n| established       = August 28, 1874\n| cathedral         = [[San Fernando Cathedral]]\n| cocathedral       = \n| patron            = \n| priests           = <!-- Number of priests in the diocese -->\n<!---- Current leadership ---->\n| pope              = {{Incumbent pope}} <!-- DO NOT CHANGE. This will update the Popes Automatically as they change -->\n| bishop            = [[Gustavo Garc\u00eda-Siller]]\n| bishop_title      = Archbishop \n| coadjutor         = \n| auxiliary_bishops = [[Michael Joseph Boulette]]<ref name=\"en.radiovaticana.va\">http://en.radiovaticana.va/news/2017/01/23/pope_appoints_new_san_antonio_auxiliary_bishop/1287572</ref>\n| vicar_general     = \n| emeritus_bishops  = \n<!---- Map ---->\n| map               = Archdiocese of San Antonio in Texas.jpg\n| map_alt           = \n| map_caption       = \n<!---- Website ---->\n| website           = [http://www.archsa.org/ archsa.org]\n| footnotes         = \n}}\nThe '''Catholic Archdiocese of San Antonio''' ([[Roman Rite]]) encompasses {{convert|27841|sqmi|km2}} in the [[U.S. state|US state]] of [[Texas]].\n\nThe archdiocese includes the city of [[San Antonio, Texas|San Antonio]] and the following counties: [[Val Verde County, Texas|Val Verde]], [[Edwards County, Texas|Edwards]], [[Kerr County, Texas|Kerr]], [[Gillespie County, Texas|Gillespie]], [[Kendall County, Texas|Kendall]], [[Comal County, Texas|Comal]], [[Guadalupe County, Texas|Guadalupe]], [[Gonzales County, Texas|Gonzales]], [[Uvalde County, Texas|Uvalde]], [[Kinney County, Texas|Kinney]], [[Medina County, Texas|Medina]], [[Bexar County, Texas|Bexar]], [[Wilson County, Texas|Wilson]], [[Karnes County, Texas|Karnes]], [[Frio County, Texas|Frio]], [[Atascosa County, Texas|Atascosa]], and the portion of [[McMullen County, Texas|McMullen]] north of the [[Nueces River]].<ref>''Official Catholic Directory Anno Domini, Part 1''. [[P.J. Kenedy]], 2005. [https://books.google.com/books?ei=36dwUPP_HIbyyAGrlIGIAw&id=dtFAAQAAIAAJ&dq=San+Antonio+Archdiocese+McMullen+Wilson+Frio&q=%22San+Antonio+archdiocese+comprises%22#search_anchor p. 1195]. Retrieved from [[Google Books]] on October 6, 2012. \"The San Antonio Archdiocese comprises Atascosa, Bandera, Bexar, Comal, Edwards, Frio, Gillespie, Gonzales, Guadalupe, Karnes, Kendall, Kerr, Kinney, McMullen (that part of McMullen County north of the Nueces River), Medina, Real, Uvalde, Vol Verde and Wilson.\"</ref>\n\nOn August 28, 1874, the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Galveston|Catholic Diocese of Galveston]] was divided and the northern territory was canonically erected by the Holy See as the diocese of San Antonio. Originally part of the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of New Orleans|Ecclesiastical Province of New Orleans]], it was subsequently elevated on August 3, 1926, to a metropolitan archdiocese.\n\nThe archbishop of San Antonio also serves as the Metropolitan of the ecclesiastical province of San Antonio with the Archdiocese of San Antonio overseeing the following [[suffragan]] dioceses: [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Amarillo|Amarillo]], [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Dallas|Dallas]], [[Roman Catholic Diocese of El Paso|El Paso]], [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Fort Worth|Fort Worth]], [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Laredo|Laredo]], [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Lubbock|Lubbock]], and [[Roman Catholic Diocese of San Angelo|San Angelo]]. All of Texas' dioceses had been suffragan sees under San Antonio until December 2004 when [[Pope John Paul II]] created the new Ecclesiastical Province of Galveston-Houston and elevated the [[Archdiocese of Galveston-Houston]] to a Metropolitan See.\n\n==History of diocese==\nThe '''Archdiocese of San Antonio''' was erected as a diocese on August 28, 1874, under the then [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Galveston-Houston|Diocese of Galveston]].<ref name=hierarchy>{{cite news|date=2010-04-06|work=Roman Catholic Archdiocese of San Antonio|title=Archdiocese of San Antonio Archidioecesis Sancti Antonii|url=http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/dsnan.html}}</ref> It was elevated to an archdiocese on August 3, 1926.<ref name=\"hierarchy\"/> As of 2010, it has 138 [[Parish (Catholic Church)|parishes]], 34 [[Catholic missions|missions]] and two [[Pastoral care#Roman Catholicism|pastoral centers]].<ref name=adsa>{{cite news|date=2010-04-06|work=Roman Catholic Archdiocese of San Antonio|title=Fast Facts|url=http://www.archdiosa.org/fast_facts.aspx}}</ref>\n\nWith the appointment of Archbishop Jos\u00e9 Horacio G\u00f3mez as the [[Coadjutor bishop|Coadjutor Archbishop of Los Angeles]], its cathedral was considered [[sede vacante]] until October 14, 2010.<ref name=\"hierarchy\"/>\n\nOn October 14, 2010, [[Pope Benedict XVI]] appointed Gustavo Garcia-Siller as archbishop of the Archdiocese of San Antonio.<ref>http://www.usccb.org/comm/archives/2010/10-179E.shtml</ref>\n\nOn January 31, 2019, the Archdiocese of San Antonio released a list of 56 Catholic clergy who were \"credibly accused\" of committing acts of sex abuse as early as 1940.<ref name=\"tpr.org\">https://www.tpr.org/post/archdiocese-san-antonio-releases-report-child-sexual-abuse-clergy</ref><ref name=\"tpr.org\"/><ref>https://www.sacurrent.com/the-daily/archives/2019/01/31/archdiocese-of-san-antonio-report-names-nearly-60-priests-accused-of-sexual-assault-since-1940s</ref>\n\n==Bishops==\nThe following are lists of ordinaries (bishops and archbishops of the diocese) and auxiliary bishops, and their years of service.  They are followed by other priests of this diocese who became bishops.\n\n===Bishops of San Antonio===\n# [[Anthony Dominic Ambrose Pellicer]] (1874\u20131880)\n# [[John Claude Neraz]] (1881\u20131894)\n# [[John Anthony Forest]] (1895\u20131911)\n# [[John Shaw (archbishop)|John William Shaw]] (1911\u20131918), appointed [[Archbishop of New Orleans]]\n# [[Arthur Jerome Drossaerts]] (1918\u20131926)\n\n===Archbishops of San Antonio===\n# [[Arthur Jerome Drossaerts]] (1926\u20131940)\n# [[Robert Emmet Lucey]] (1941\u20131969)\n# [[Francis James Furey]] (1969\u20131979)\n# [[Patrick Fern\u00e1ndez Flores]] (1979\u20132004)\n# [[Jos\u00e9 Horacio G\u00f3mez]] (2004\u20132010), appointed Coadjutor Archbishop and later [[Archbishop of Los Angeles]]<ref name=usccb>{{cite news|date=2010-04-06|work=[[United States Conference of Catholic Bishops]]|title=Pope Names San Antonio Archbishop Jos\u00e9 Gomez Coadjutor Archbishop Of Los Angeles|url=http://www.usccb.org/comm/archives/2010/10-061.shtml}}</ref><ref name=archla>{{cite news|date=2010-04-02|work=[[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Los Angeles]]|title=POPE APPOINTS COADJUTOR ARCHBISHOP FOR LOS ANGELES|url=http://www.archdiocese.la/news/story.php?newsid=1169|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100409131310/http://www.archdiocese.la/news/story.php?newsid=1169|archivedate=2010-04-09}}</ref>\n# [[Gustavo Garcia-Siller]], M.Sp.S. (2010\u2013present)\n\n===Coadjutor Bishops===\n* [[John Shaw (archbishop)|John William Shaw]] (1910-1911)\n\n===Auxiliary Bishops===\n* [[Stephen Aloysius Leven]] (1955-1969), appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of San Angelo|Bishop of San Angelo]]\n* [[Patrick Flores|Patrick Fern\u00e1ndez Flores]] (1970-1978), appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of El Paso|Bishop of El Paso]] and later Archbishop of San Antonio\n* [[Hugo Mark Gerbermann]], [[Maryknoll|M.M.]] (1975-1982)\n* [[Raymundo Joseph Pe\u00f1a]] (1976-1980), appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of El Paso|Bishop of El Paso]] and later [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Brownsville|Bishop of Brownsville]]\n* [[Charles Victor Grahmann]] (1981-1982), appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Victoria in Texas|Bishop of Victoria]] and later [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Dallas|Bishop of Dallas]]\n* [[Ricardo Ramirez]], [[Congregation of St. Basil|C.S.B]] (1981-1982), appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Las Cruces|Bishop of Las Cruces]]\n* [[Bernard Ferdinand Popp]] (1983-1993)\n* [[Edmond Carmody]] (1988-1992), appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Tyler|Bishop of Tyler]] and later [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Corpus Christi|Bishop of Corpus Christi]]\n* [[Joseph Anthony Galante]] (1992-1994), appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Beaumont|Bishop of Beaumont]] and later [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Dallas|Coadjutor Bishop of Dallas]] and [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Camden|Bishop of Camden]]\n* [[John Yanta]] (1994-1997), appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Amarillo|Bishop of Amarillo]]\n* [[Thomas Flanagan (bishop)|Thomas Flanagan]] (1998-2005)\n* [[Patrick Zurek]] (1998-2008), appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Amarillo|Bishop of Amarillo]]\n* [[Oscar Cant\u00fa]] (2008-2013), appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Las Cruces|Bishop of Las Cruces]]\n* [[Michael Joseph Boulette]]<ref name=\"en.radiovaticana.va\">http://en.radiovaticana.va/news/2017/01/23/pope_appoints_new_san_antonio_auxiliary_bishop/1287572</ref> (2017\u2013present)\n\n===Other priests of this diocese who became bishops===\n* [[Mariano Simon Garriga]], appointed Coadjutor Bishop in 1936 and later [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Corpus Christi|Bishop of Corpus Christi]]\n* [[Sidney Matthew Metzger]], appointed [[Archdiocese of Santa Fe|Auxiliary Bishop of Santa Fe]] in 1939 and later Coadjutor Bishop and [[Roman Catholic Diocese of El Paso|Bishop of El Paso]]\n* [[Laurence Julius FitzSimon]], appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Amarillo|Bishop of Amarillo]] in 1941\n* [[John Louis Morkovsky]], appointed Auxiliary Bishop of Amarillo in 1955, later Bishop of Amarillo, Coadjutor Bishop of Galveston-Houston, Bishop of Galveston-Houston\n* [[Charles Edwin Herzig]], appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Tyler|Bishop of Tyler]] in 1986\n* [[Gerald Richard Barnes]], appointed Auxiliary Bishop in 1992 and later [[Roman Catholic Diocese of San Bernardino|Bishop of San Bernardino]]\n* [[Arturo Cepeda|Jos\u00e9 Arturo Cepeda Escobedo]], appointed [[Archdiocese of Detroit|Auxiliary Bishop of Detroit]] in 2011\n\n==Education==\n===Universities===\n* [[University of the Incarnate Word]] (est. 1881)\n* [[Our Lady of the Lake University]] (est. 1895)\n* [[St. Mary's University, Texas|St. Mary's University]] (est. 1852)\n\n===High schools===\n* [[Antonian College Preparatory High School]], Castle Hills (Est. 1964)\n* [[Central Catholic Marianist High School]], San Antonio (Est. 1852)\n* [[Holy Cross of San Antonio]], San Antonio (Est. 1957)\n* [[Incarnate Word High School]], San Antonio (Est. 1881)\n* [[Our Lady of the Hills High School]], Kerrville (Est. 2013)\n* [[Providence High School (San Antonio)|Providence High School]], San Antonio (Est. 1951)\n* [[St. Anthony Catholic High School]], San Antonio (Est. 1903)\n* [[St. Gerard Catholic High School]], San Antonio (Est. 1927)\n* [[John Paul II Catholic High School (Texas)|John Paul II Catholic High School]], Schertz (Est. 2009)\n\n===Former schools===\n* [[St. Francis Academy (San Antonio)|St. Francis Academy]] - High school for girls<!--https://web.archive.org/web/20010222121008/http://www.sacatholicschools.org/highschools.shtml and https://web.archive.org/web/20010501165541/http://www.geocities.com/stfacademy/ -->\n* [[St. Mary's School by the Riverwalk]] (1910&ndash;2004)\n\n==Province of San Antonio==\nSee ''[[List of the Catholic bishops of the United States#Province of San Antonio|List of the Catholic bishops of the United States]]''\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Catholicism|Texas}}\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* [[Catholic Church by country]]\n* [[Catholic Church in the United States]]\n* [[List of the Catholic dioceses of the United States#Ecclesiastical province of San Antonio|Ecclesiastical Province of San Antonio]]\n* [[Global organisation of the Catholic Church]]\n* [[List of Roman Catholic archdioceses]] (by country and continent)\n* [[List of Roman Catholic dioceses (alphabetical)]] (including archdioceses)\n* [[List of Roman Catholic dioceses (structured view)]] (including archdioceses)\n* [[List of the Catholic dioceses of the United States]]\n{{div col end}}\n<!-- please keep entries in alphabetical order -->\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.archsa.org/ Roman Catholic Archdiocese of San Antonio Official Site]\n** [https://web.archive.org/*/http://www.archdiosa.org/ Roman Catholic Archdiocese of San Antonio Official Site] (Archive)\n* [http://www.sacatholicschools.org/ Archdiocese of San Antonio Schools]\n* [https://web.archive.org/*/http://www.archdiosa.org/ Archdiocese of San Antonio] (Archives)\n* {{cite web|url=http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/13424b.htm|title=Diocese of San Antonio|work=[[Catholic Encyclopedia]]}}\n\n{{Roman Catholic Archdiocese of San Antonio}}\n{{Roman Catholic Ecclesiastical Province of San Antonio}}\n{{R-C provinces in the United States}}\n{{coord|29.4246|N|98.4942|W|source:wikidata|display=title}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Roman Catholic Archdiocese Of San Antonio}}\n[[Category:Roman Catholic Archdiocese of San Antonio| ]]\n[[Category:Organizations based in San Antonio]]\n[[Category:Roman Catholic dioceses and prelatures established in the 19th century|San Antonio]]\n[[Category:Roman Catholic dioceses in the United States|San Antonio]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox diocese\n| jurisdiction      = Archdiocese<!-- Type of jurisdiction: i.e. Diocese or Archdiocese -->\n| name              = San Antonio\n| latin             = Archidioecesis Sancti Antonii\n| local             = <!-- Name in the Spanish language -->Arquidi\u00f3cesis de San Antonio\n| image             = San Fernando Cathedral.jpg\n| image_size        = 250px \n| image_alt         = \n| caption           = San Fernando Cathedral\n| coat              = Roman Catholic Archdiocese of San Antonio.svg\n| coat_size         = 150px \n<!---- Locations ---->\n| country           = [[United States]]\n| territory         = City of [[San Antonio, Texas|San Antonio]] and the following counties: [[Val Verde County, Texas|Val Verde]], [[Edwards County, Texas|Edwards]], [[Kerr County, Texas|Kerr]], [[Gillespie County, Texas|Gillespie]], [[Kendall County, Texas|Kendall]], [[Comal County, Texas|Comal]], [[Guadalupe County, Texas|Guadalupe]], [[Gonzales County, Texas|Gonzales]], [[Uvalde County, Texas|Uvalde]], [[Kinney County, Texas|Kinney]], [[Medina County, Texas|Medina]], [[Bexar County, Texas|Bexar]], [[Wilson County, Texas|Wilson]], [[Karnes County, Texas|Karnes]], [[Frio County, Texas|Frio]], [[Atascosa County, Texas|Atascosa]], and [[McMullen County, Texas|McMullen]].\n| province          = [[List of the Roman Catholic dioceses of the United States#Ecclesiastical_province_of_San_Antonio|Province of San Antonio]]\n| coordinates       = <!-- Use {{coord}} --> \n<!---- Statistics ---->\n| area_sqmi         = 27841<!-- Area in square miles, automatically converted -->\n| population        = 2,458,351\n| population_as_of  = 2014\n| catholics         = 728,001<ref>http://www.archsa.org/fast_facts.aspx</ref><!-- Number of Catholics in the diocese -->\n| catholics_percent = 29.6\n| parishes          = 139\n| churches          = <!-- Number of churches in the diocese -->\n| congregations     = <!-- Number of congregations in the diocese -->\n| schools           = <!-- Number of church supported schools in the diocese -->\n| members           = <!-- Number of members in the diocese -->\n<!---- Information ---->\n| denomination      = [[Catholic]]\n| rite              = [[Roman Rite]]\n| established       = August 28, 1874\n| cathedral         = [[San Fernando Cathedral]]\n| cocathedral       = \n| patron            = \n| priests           = <!-- Number of priests in the diocese -->\n<!---- Current leadership ---->\n| pope              = {{Incumbent pope}} <!-- DO NOT CHANGE. This will update the Popes Automatically as they change -->\n| bishop            = [[Gustavo Garc\u00eda-Siller]]\n| bishop_title      = Archbishop \n| coadjutor         = \n| auxiliary_bishops = [[Michael Joseph Boulette]]<ref>http://en.radiovaticana.va/news/2017/01/23/pope_appoints_new_san_antonio_auxiliary_bishop/1287572</ref>\n| vicar_general     = \n| emeritus_bishops  = \n<!---- Map ---->\n| map               = Archdiocese of San Antonio in Texas.jpg\n| map_alt           = \n| map_caption       = \n<!---- Website ---->\n| website           = [http://www.archsa.org/ archsa.org]\n| footnotes         = \n}}\nThe '''Catholic Archdiocese of San Antonio''' ([[Roman Rite]]) encompasses {{convert|27841|sqmi|km2}} in the [[U.S. state|US state]] of [[Texas]].\n\nThe archdiocese includes the city of [[San Antonio, Texas|San Antonio]] and the following counties: [[Val Verde County, Texas|Val Verde]], [[Edwards County, Texas|Edwards]], [[Kerr County, Texas|Kerr]], [[Gillespie County, Texas|Gillespie]], [[Kendall County, Texas|Kendall]], [[Comal County, Texas|Comal]], [[Guadalupe County, Texas|Guadalupe]], [[Gonzales County, Texas|Gonzales]], [[Uvalde County, Texas|Uvalde]], [[Kinney County, Texas|Kinney]], [[Medina County, Texas|Medina]], [[Bexar County, Texas|Bexar]], [[Wilson County, Texas|Wilson]], [[Karnes County, Texas|Karnes]], [[Frio County, Texas|Frio]], [[Atascosa County, Texas|Atascosa]], and the portion of [[McMullen County, Texas|McMullen]] north of the [[Nueces River]].<ref>''Official Catholic Directory Anno Domini, Part 1''. [[P.J. Kenedy]], 2005. [https://books.google.com/books?ei=36dwUPP_HIbyyAGrlIGIAw&id=dtFAAQAAIAAJ&dq=San+Antonio+Archdiocese+McMullen+Wilson+Frio&q=%22San+Antonio+archdiocese+comprises%22#search_anchor p. 1195]. Retrieved from [[Google Books]] on October 6, 2012. \"The San Antonio Archdiocese comprises Atascosa, Bandera, Bexar, Comal, Edwards, Frio, Gillespie, Gonzales, Guadalupe, Karnes, Kendall, Kerr, Kinney, McMullen (that part of McMullen County north of the Nueces River), Medina, Real, Uvalde, Vol Verde and Wilson.\"</ref>\n\nOn August 28, 1874, the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Galveston|Catholic Diocese of Galveston]] was divided and the northern territory was canonically erected by the Holy See as the diocese of San Antonio. Originally part of the [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of New Orleans|Ecclesiastical Province of New Orleans]], it was subsequently elevated on August 3, 1926, to a metropolitan archdiocese.\n\nThe archbishop of San Antonio also serves as the Metropolitan of the ecclesiastical province of San Antonio with the Archdiocese of San Antonio overseeing the following [[suffragan]] dioceses: [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Amarillo|Amarillo]], [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Dallas|Dallas]], [[Roman Catholic Diocese of El Paso|El Paso]], [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Fort Worth|Fort Worth]], [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Laredo|Laredo]], [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Lubbock|Lubbock]], and [[Roman Catholic Diocese of San Angelo|San Angelo]]. All of Texas' dioceses had been suffragan sees under San Antonio until December 2004 when [[Pope John Paul II]] created the new Ecclesiastical Province of Galveston-Houston and elevated the [[Archdiocese of Galveston-Houston]] to a Metropolitan See.\n\n==History of diocese==\nThe '''Archdiocese of San Antonio''' was erected as a diocese on August 28, 1874, under the then [[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Galveston-Houston|Diocese of Galveston]].<ref name=hierarchy>{{cite news|date=2010-04-06|work=Roman Catholic Archdiocese of San Antonio|title=Archdiocese of San Antonio Archidioecesis Sancti Antonii|url=http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/diocese/dsnan.html}}</ref> It was elevated to an archdiocese on August 3, 1926.<ref name=\"hierarchy\"/> As of 2010, it has 138 [[Parish (Catholic Church)|parishes]], 34 [[Catholic missions|missions]] and two [[Pastoral_care#Roman_Catholicism|pastoral centers]].<ref name=adsa>{{cite news|date=2010-04-06|work=Roman Catholic Archdiocese of San Antonio|title=Fast Facts|url=http://www.archdiosa.org/fast_facts.aspx}}</ref>\n\nWith the appointment of Archbishop Jos\u00e9 Horacio G\u00f3mez as the [[Coadjutor bishop|Coadjutor Archbishop of Los Angeles]], its cathedral was considered [[sede vacante]] until October 14, 2010.<ref name=\"hierarchy\"/> \n\nOn October 14, 2010, [[Pope Benedict XVI]] appointed Gustavo Garcia-Siller as archbishop of the Archdiocese of San Antonio.<ref>http://www.usccb.org/comm/archives/2010/10-179E.shtml</ref>\n\nOn January 31, 2019, the Archdiocese of San Antonio released a list of 56 Catholic clergy who were \"credibly accused\" of committing acts of sex abuse as early as 1940.<ref>https://www.tpr.org/post/archdiocese-san-antonio-releases-report-child-sexual-abuse-clergy</ref><ref>https://www.tpr.org/post/archdiocese-san-antonio-releases-report-child-sexual-abuse-clergy</ref><ref>https://www.sacurrent.com/the-daily/archives/2019/01/31/archdiocese-of-san-antonio-report-names-nearly-60-priests-accused-of-sexual-assault-since-1940s</ref>\n\n==Bishops==\nThe following are lists of ordinaries (bishops and archbishops of the diocese) and auxiliary bishops, and their years of service.  They are followed by other priests of this diocese who became bishops.\n\n===Bishops of San Antonio===\n# [[Anthony Dominic Ambrose Pellicer]] (1874\u20131880)\n# [[John Claude Neraz]] (1881\u20131894)\n# [[John Anthony Forest]] (1895\u20131911)\n# [[John Shaw (archbishop)|John William Shaw]] (1911\u20131918), appointed [[Archbishop of New Orleans]]\n# [[Arthur Jerome Drossaerts]] (1918\u20131926)\n\n===Archbishops of San Antonio===\n# [[Arthur Jerome Drossaerts]] (1926\u20131940)\n# [[Robert Emmet Lucey]] (1941\u20131969)\n# [[Francis James Furey]] (1969\u20131979)\n# [[Patrick Fern\u00e1ndez Flores]] (1979\u20132004)\n# [[Jos\u00e9 Horacio G\u00f3mez]] (2004\u20132010), appointed Coadjutor Archbishop and later [[Archbishop of Los Angeles]]<ref name=usccb>{{cite news|date=2010-04-06|work=[[United States Conference of Catholic Bishops]]|title=Pope Names San Antonio Archbishop Jos\u00e9 Gomez Coadjutor Archbishop Of Los Angeles|url=http://www.usccb.org/comm/archives/2010/10-061.shtml}}</ref><ref name=archla>{{cite news|date=2010-04-02|work=[[Roman Catholic Archdiocese of Los Angeles]]|title=POPE APPOINTS COADJUTOR ARCHBISHOP FOR LOS ANGELES|url=http://www.archdiocese.la/news/story.php?newsid=1169|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100409131310/http://www.archdiocese.la/news/story.php?newsid=1169|archivedate=2010-04-09}}</ref>\n# [[Gustavo Garcia-Siller]], M.Sp.S. (2010\u2013present)\n\n===Coadjutor Bishops===\n* [[John Shaw (archbishop)|John William Shaw]] (1910-1911)\n\n===Auxiliary Bishops===\n* [[Stephen Aloysius Leven]] (1955-1969), appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of San Angelo|Bishop of San Angelo]]\n* [[Patrick Flores|Patrick Fern\u00e1ndez Flores]] (1970-1978), appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of El Paso|Bishop of El Paso]] and later Archbishop of San Antonio\n* [[Hugo Mark Gerbermann]], [[Maryknoll|M.M.]] (1975-1982)\n* [[Raymundo Joseph Pe\u00f1a]] (1976-1980), appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of El Paso|Bishop of El Paso]] and later [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Brownsville|Bishop of Brownsville]]\n* [[Charles Victor Grahmann]] (1981-1982), appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Victoria in Texas|Bishop of Victoria]] and later [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Dallas|Bishop of Dallas]]\n* [[Ricardo Ramirez]], [[Congregation of St. Basil|C.S.B]] (1981-1982), appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Las Cruces|Bishop of Las Cruces]]\n* [[Bernard Ferdinand Popp]] (1983-1993)\n* [[Edmond Carmody]] (1988-1992), appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Tyler|Bishop of Tyler]] and later [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Corpus Christi|Bishop of Corpus Christi]]\n* [[Joseph Anthony Galante]] (1992-1994), appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Beaumont|Bishop of Beaumont]] and later [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Dallas|Coadjutor Bishop of Dallas]] and [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Camden|Bishop of Camden]]\n* [[John Yanta]] (1994-1997), appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Amarillo|Bishop of Amarillo]]\n* [[Thomas Flanagan (bishop)|Thomas Flanagan]] (1998-2005)\n* [[Patrick Zurek]] (1998-2008), appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Amarillo|Bishop of Amarillo]]\n* [[Oscar Cant\u00fa]] (2008-2013), appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Las Cruces|Bishop of Las Cruces]]\n* [[Michael Joseph Boulette]]<ref>http://en.radiovaticana.va/news/2017/01/23/pope_appoints_new_san_antonio_auxiliary_bishop/1287572</ref> (2017-present)\n\n===Other priests of this diocese who became bishops===\n* [[Mariano Simon Garriga]], appointed Coadjutor Bishop in 1936 and later [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Corpus Christi|Bishop of Corpus Christi]]\n* [[Sidney Matthew Metzger]], appointed [[Archdiocese of Santa Fe|Auxiliary Bishop of Santa Fe]] in 1939 and later Coadjutor Bishop and [[Roman Catholic Diocese of El Paso|Bishop of El Paso]]\n* [[Laurence Julius FitzSimon]], appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Amarillo|Bishop of Amarillo]] in 1941\n* [[John Louis Morkovsky]], appointed Auxiliary Bishop of Amarillo in 1955, later Bishop of Amarillo, Coadjutor Bishop of Galveston-Houston, Bishop of Galveston-Houston\n* [[Charles Edwin Herzig]], appointed [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Tyler|Bishop of Tyler]] in 1986\n* [[Gerald Richard Barnes]], appointed Auxiliary Bishop in 1992 and later [[Roman Catholic Diocese of San Bernardino|Bishop of San Bernardino]]\n* [[Arturo Cepeda|Jos\u00e9 Arturo Cepeda Escobedo]], appointed [[Archdiocese of Detroit|Auxiliary Bishop of Detroit]] in 2011\n\n==Education==\n===Universities===\n* [[University of the Incarnate Word]] (est. 1881)\n* [[Our Lady of the Lake University]] (est. 1895)\n* [[St. Mary's University, Texas|St. Mary's University]] (est. 1852)\n\n===High schools===\n* [[Antonian College Preparatory High School]], Castle Hills (Est. 1964)\n* [[Central Catholic Marianist High School]], San Antonio (Est. 1852)\n* [[Holy Cross of San Antonio]], San Antonio (Est. 1957)\n* [[Incarnate Word High School]], San Antonio (Est. 1881)\n* [[Our Lady of the Hills High School]], Kerrville (Est. 2013)\n* [[Providence High School (San Antonio)|Providence High School]], San Antonio (Est. 1951)\n* [[St. Anthony Catholic High School]], San Antonio (Est. 1903)\n* [[St. Gerard Catholic High School]], San Antonio (Est. 1927)\n* [[John Paul II Catholic High School (Texas)|John Paul II Catholic High School]], Schertz (Est. 2009)\n\n===Former schools===\n* [[St. Francis Academy (San Antonio)|St. Francis Academy]] - High school for girls<!--https://web.archive.org/web/20010222121008/http://www.sacatholicschools.org/highschools.shtml and https://web.archive.org/web/20010501165541/http://www.geocities.com/stfacademy/ -->\n* [[St. Mary's School by the Riverwalk]] (1910&ndash;2004)\n\n==Province of San Antonio==\nSee ''[[List of the Catholic bishops of the United States#Province of San Antonio|List of the Catholic bishops of the United States]]''\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Catholicism|Texas}}\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n* [[Catholic Church by country]]\n* [[Catholic Church in the United States]]\n* [[List_of_the_Catholic_dioceses_of_the_United_States#Ecclesiastical_province_of_San_Antonio|Ecclesiastical Province of San Antonio]]\n* [[Global organisation of the Catholic Church]]\n* [[List of Roman Catholic archdioceses]] (by country and continent)\n* [[List of Roman Catholic dioceses (alphabetical)]] (including archdioceses)\n* [[List of Roman Catholic dioceses (structured view)]] (including archdioceses)\n* [[List of the Catholic dioceses of the United States]]\n{{div col end}}\n<!-- please keep entries in alphabetical order -->\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.archsa.org/ Roman Catholic Archdiocese of San Antonio Official Site]\n** [https://web.archive.org/*/http://www.archdiosa.org/ Roman Catholic Archdiocese of San Antonio Official Site] (Archive)\n* [http://www.sacatholicschools.org/ Archdiocese of Sa