er <small>(2006\u20132009)</small>\n* C.Smith <small>(2006\u20132009)</small>\n* DJ Don Juan <small>(2006\u20132010)</small>\n* Tic Toc <small>(2006\u20132009)</small>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{No Limit Records}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Medicine Men}}\n[[Category:American hip hop groups]]\n[[Category:Southern hip hop groups]]\n[[Category:Tommy Boy Records artists]]\n[[Category:No Limit Records artists]]\n[[Category:American hip hop record producers]]\n[[Category:Record production teams]]\n", "text_old": "::''For other uses, see [[Medicine Man (disambiguation)]]'' \n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name                = The Medicine Men\n| background          = non_performing_personnel\n| image               = \n| caption             = \n| origin              = [[New Orleans, Louisiana]], United States\n| genre               = [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]], [[hip hop soul]], [[jazz rap]], [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n| occupation          = [[Record producer|Record production team]]<br />[[Songwriter|Songwriting team]]\n| instrument          = \n| years_active        = 1995-present\n| label               = {{flatlist|\n* BBTP Music <small>(current)</small>\n* [[No Limit Records|No Limit]]\n* [[Priority Records|Priority]]\n* [[EMI Records|EMI]]\n* Overdose\n* [[Tommy Boy Entertainment|Tommy Boy]]\n* [[Warner Bros. Records|Warner Bros.]]\n* [[Asylum Records|Asylum]]\n }}\n| associated_acts     = <!-- Exercise constraint and add only the NOTABLE acts associated with 808 Mafia; see [[Template:Infobox musical artist#Associated acts]] for criteria -->[[TRU (group)|TRU]], [[Mia X]], [[Fiend (rapper)|Fiend]], [[Mystikal]], [[Snoop Dogg]], [[UGK]], [[Bone Thugs-n-Harmony]], [[Montell Jordan]], [[Destiny's Child]], [[Mariah Carey]], [[Foxy Brown (rapper)]], [[Big Pun]], [[M\u00fda]], [[Charlie Wilson (singer)]]\n| website             = http://beatsbythepound.com/  https://bbtpmusic.bandcamp.com/ \n| Current_members     = [[KLC]]<br/>[[Mo B. Dick]]<br/>Craig B<br/>[[Odell (producer)|O'Dell]]\n| Past_members     = [[Carlos Stephens]]<br/>D. Bazile<br/>DJ Don Juan<br/>Elvin Presley<br/>Richard Weber\n}}\n'''The Medicine Men''' (formerly known as '''Beats by the Pound''') are a [[Louisiana]]-based American music production team made up of four men.<ref name=rapcoalition>{{cite web| url = http://www.rapcoalition.org/update_june_2000.htm | title = Rap Coalition update 2000 | accessdate = 2006-09-09 }}</ref>\n\nThe collective, with the members ([[KLC]], [[Mo B. Dick]], Craig B, O'Dell) helped sell 30 million records for [[Master P]]'s [[No Limit Records]], from 1995 to 1999, as well the majority of releases from [[No Limit Records]] during the days it was distributed by [[Priority Records]].<ref name=Vh1>{{cite web| url = http://www.vh1.com/artists/az/master_p/bio.jhtml| title = Vh1 Master P Biography| accessdate = 2006-09-09}}</ref><ref name=Vh1/><ref name=AMG>{{cite web| url = {{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p355353|pure_url=yes}}| title = Allmusic Guide for Beats by the Pound| accessdate = 2006-09-09}}</ref> They would later receive nomination for Producers of the Year and collectively be voted as one of Hip-Hop's \"Thirty Most Powerful People\" by The Source in 1999. From 1995 to 1999 many of The Medicine Men productions feature hooks from [[Mo B. Dick]] or [[Odell (producer)|O'Dell]] credited as a featured artist.<ref name=Vh1/>\n\n== Singles produced ==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of singles produced, with selected chart positions and certifications, showing year released and album name\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:20em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"3\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:12em;\" | [[List of music recording certifications|Certifications]]\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:90%;\"|[[Billboard Hot 100|US]]\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;fon