archdiocese was erected in the 1st century as a [[diocese]], and was elevated to an [[archdiocese]] in the 6th century.<ref name=CathHierRavenna /> Among its famous archbishops are Saint [[Peter Chrysologus]], a [[Doctor of the Church]], and Saint [[Guido Maria Conforti]], who was canonized as a saint in 2011 by [[Pope Benedict XVI]]. The early medieval [[Ravenna papyri]] form an important record from the church's chancery between the 5th and 10th century.\n\nThe archdiocese was created in 1947 through the merger of the [[Archdiocese of Ravenna]] and the [[Diocese of Cervia]].<ref name=CathHierRavenna />  The archdiocese in 2014 had one priest for every 1,830 Catholics.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[Bishop of Ravenna]], for a complete list of bishops\n\n== References ==\n<references/>\n\n== Further reading ==\n* [[Andreas Agnellus|Agnellus, Andreas]] (1708); Bacchini, Benedetto (ed.) Agnelli Liber Pontificalis, sive; Vit\u00e6 Pontificum Ravennatum Mutin\u00e6: Typis Antonii Capponii ..., MDCCVIII. 2 pt. ([16], 372, 164 p. [12] leaves of plates (incl. fontispiece, 11 folded); 503, [1] p., [1] leaf of plates : ill., geneal. tables; 4to.\n**Later editions 1723; in Patrologia Latina; and 2006\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/diocese/rave0.htm Metropolitan Archdiocese of Ravenna-Cervia]\n\n{{Roman Catholic Ecclesiastical Province of Ravenna}}\n\n{{coord|44.4167|N|12.2000|E|source:wikidata-and-enwiki-cat-tree_region:IT|display=title}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ravenna-Cervia, Archdiocese}}\n[[Category:Roman Catholic dioceses in Emilia-Romagna]]\n[[Category:Dioceses established in the 1st century]]\n\n\n{{Italy-RC-diocese-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{refimprove|date=October 2016}}\n\n{{Infobox diocese\n| jurisdiction      = Archdiocese<!-- Type of jurisdiction: i.e. Diocese or Archdiocese -->\n| name              = Ravenna-Cervia\n| latin             = Archidioecesis Ravennatensis-Cerviensis\n| local             = <!-- Name in the nati